CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 28, 1958, pg. A3 reads: "Lutherans Confer - During the recent meeting of the Eastern District of the Lutheran Church, Missouri Synod, at Chatham College, Miss Rosa J. Young, seated, center, a pioneer Lutheran missionary of Selma, Ala., held a sideline conference with local Lutheran leaders. Left to right: Mrs. John Fey, the Rev. John Fey, pastor of Faith Lutheran Church, and Mrs. Bernice D. Stewart, extreme right.  Mmes. Fey and Stewart were official delegates from Faith Church. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Mrs. John Fey, Rev. John Fey, Rosa J. Young, and Bernice D. Stewart, gathered in interior at Chatham College for Lutheran Church conference
